rence\": 0.68,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.82,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.55,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.61,\n      \"feedback\": \"This branch is conceptually based on Kim-Benner ribosylation, but the implementation is chemically inaccurate. Kim and Benner obtained a 2'-phosphate NMN-like product from nicotinamide plus ribose-1,2-cyclic phosphate under evaporative Mg2+/Ca2+ conditions, not free nicotinamide riboside as written. The stated product identity in rxn_024 therefore deviates substantially from the literature.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_024\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Replace rxn_024 with formation of the 2'-phosphate regioisomer rather than nicotinamide riboside.\",\n        \"Include Mg2+ or Ca2+, 85C, and evaporative conditions explicitly to align with Kim-Benner.\",\n        \"Avoid implying a direct route to biologically relevant NMN from this step.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.28,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.95,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.95,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.96,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.9\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.74,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.8,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.83,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.93,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.76,\n      \"feedback\": \"The downstream logic into the Orgel route is good, but the feedstock-generating step is the major weakness. Surface conversion of acetate and ammonia into cyanoacetylene plus HCN is not the literature-supported Patel-Sutherland chemistry; cyanoacetylene is instead tied to HCN plus acetylene under Cu(I)-mediated conditions. Because the network places the critical nexus molecule on a weak foundation, this pathway is only moderately credible overall.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\":